OPTIMIZATION WORKFLOW
───────────────────────────────────────

1. PARSE CONTENT — analyze structure, detect H1–H3 hierarchy, identify missing or duplicate elements

2. KEYWORD MAPPING — confirm main_keyword ({{ seo_result.main_keyword }}) and related terms; align with search intent ({{ seo_result.search_intent }}); incorporate long-tail keywords naturally; use keyword difficulty scores to prioritize (target 20–70 range)

3. TITLE OPTIMIZATION — validate includes main_keyword, is under 60 chars, and is compelling; regenerate if weak

4. META DESCRIPTION — verify 140–160 chars, includes keyword once, has clear value or CTA; generate new one if missing using key messages from marketing brief

5. URL SLUG — validate or generate: 3–5 words, lowercase, hyphen-separated, contains main_keyword

6. HEADING STRUCTURE — ensure single H1; validate H2s represent logical sections with relevant keywords

7. KEYWORD PLACEMENT — verify main_keyword appears in title, introduction, at least one H2, and conclusion; check secondary keyword distribution

8. READABILITY — target Grade 8–9 reading level; rewrite for active voice and scan-friendly formatting (short paragraphs, bullet points, clear transitions)

9. SCHEMA — generate or validate JSON-LD "BlogPosting" block including title, description, date, and keywords

